headline: GM faces class action in Australia over Holden transmission issues
summary: The class action covers people who bought certain models of Holden vehicles between Jan. 1, 2011 and Dec. 24, 2024, Maurice Blackburn said in a statement on Wednesday.  The alleged defect resulted in various problems, including intermittent transmission shudders and leakage of automatic transmission fluid, Maurice Blackburn said.
